  A specification specifies the <em>goals of implementation</em>,
  which becomes a <em>normative description of a production
  release</em>. A <em>draft</em> specification is not yet implemented
  and may potentially change. A <em>release draft</em> is thought to
  be internally consistent and complete and is not expected to change. A <div>final draft</div> is one that is fully implemented and 

